Package: scorematchingad
Title: Score Matching Estimation by Automatic Differentiation
Version: 0.0.0.52
Authors@R: 
    c(person(given = "Kassel Liam", family = "Hingee", email = "kassel.hingee@anu.edu.au", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9894-2407")),
    person("Janice", "Scealy", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9718-869X")),
    person("Bradley M.", "Bell", role = c("cph"))
    )
Description: Hyv√§rinen's score matching <http://jmlr.org/papers/v6/hyvarinen05a.html> is a useful estimation technique when the normalising constant for a probability distribution is difficult to compute.  This package implements score matching estimators using automatic differentiation in the CppAD library <https://github.com/coin-or/CppAD> and is designed for quickly implementing score matching estimators. General Windham robustification <https://www.jstor.org/stable/2346159> is also available. Already in the package are estimators for directional distributions (Mardia, Kent and Laha (2016) <arXiv:1604.08470>) and the flexible Polynomially-Tilted Pairwise Interaction (PPI) model for compositional data.  The latter estimators perform well when there are zeros, even many zeros (Scealy and Wood, 2023 <doi:10.1080/01621459.2021.2016422>; Scealy, Hingee, Kent, and Wood, 2024, accepted article).
